            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "The TUI can support this with the OSC 22 escape sequence, which is supported by at least Kitty and a few other terminals https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/pointer-shapes/\n\nThe list of cursor shapes supported by that protocol is [here](https://sw.kovidgoyal.net/kitty/pointer-shapes/#pointer-shape-names). Vim has a different list of names. The list in kitty's document is based on the `cursor` property from the [CSS standard](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/CSS/cursor).\n\nI think we should not enforce a static list of names, but allow users to specify whichever shape name they want (linking to the kitty document above for examples). That way GUIs can implement their own shapes if they want to. But the TUI would only support the shapes listed by the kitty protocol.",
