            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "`mode_info_set` might not be is good enough for a GUI, due to the lag. The cursor needs to respond quickly on mouse movements, when hovering over links or splits for example. And especially if nvim is running on a remote server it can take relatively long for the roundtrip needed. Furhermore it would depend on `mousemoveevent` being enabled all the time which causes a lot of RPC traffic.\n\nThat was one of the motivations for the rejected `ext_elementtype`, https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/28016. But I still think that something similar is needed.\n\n",
            "created_at": "2025-01-08T02:17:59Z",
